You are building a logistics company landing page for MultiSped, a Macedonian freight forwarding company. The project is a Next.js 14 App Router application, written in TypeScript, styled with Tailwind CSS and shadcn/ui components, with Macedonian and English translations via next-intl.

The repo starts completely empty. When the user asks you to initialise the project, run these commands in order:
npx create-next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir=false --import-alias="@/*"
npx shadcn-ui@latest init
npm install next-intl framer-motion lucide-react react-hook-form zod @hookform/resolvers d3 topojson-client
npm install -D @types/d3 @types/topojson-client

---

## Project structure

Always follow this folder structure exactly. Never deviate from it without asking:

app/
  [locale]/
    layout.tsx
    page.tsx
  globals.css
components/
  ui/                      ← shadcn/ui only, never edit manually
  layout/
    Navbar.tsx
    Footer.tsx
  sections/
    Hero.tsx
    About.tsx
    Services.tsx
    ServiceItems.tsx
    Sectors.tsx
    Map.tsx
    Contact.tsx
lib/
  utils.ts
messages/
  mk.json
  en.json
public/
  hero-frames/             ← JPEG sequence, frame-0001.jpg to frame-XXXX.jpg
tokens-ms.json
tailwind.config.ts
middleware.ts

---

## Components

Always use shadcn/ui for every component. Never build a button, input, form, card, badge, or any UI primitive from scratch. If a shadcn component exists for the job, use it. Add components via the CLI: npx shadcn-ui@latest add [component].

The only things you build custom are the section-level layout components (Hero, About, Services, etc.) which compose shadcn primitives inside them.

Never modify files inside components/ui/ by hand. Style overrides go in the consuming component using Tailwind classes.

---

## Design tokens and CSS variables

The file tokens-ms.json is the single source of truth for all design decisions. Never hardcode a color, spacing value, border radius, or shadow anywhere in the codebase. Always use CSS variables.

Declare all CSS variables in app/globals.css like this:

